This is nothing new. It's the way the world is, and most of us are fine with it. When this new medical technology becomes available, we'll all benefit from it, and some will benefit from it more than others. But they'll be the same people they've always been. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udryfft.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dryfft</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 1:13:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT:  Cloning</span><hr size=1> There is more to this than jealousy and science fiction.  You people don't seem to be trying to see beyond that.<br>
<br>
If I can think of applications of genetic engineering, others will too.  <br>
<br>
When you are sitting there thinking &quot;it will never happen&quot;, there are people out there thinking &quot;this is gonna be great&quot;.<br>
<br>
I don't believe I can ever get you people to see what I think, let alone agree with me.  But it doesn't matter anyway.  What will happen, will happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=liquid>Liquid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 1:13:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT:  Cloning</span><hr size=1> Quote:<br>
------------------------------------------------<br>
Being against a whole set of engineered beings WILL cause war because it creates an obvious line between the engineered people and the ones who aren't. It's inevitable, whereas with a concept, people can argue, and their actions aren't constantly IN YOUR FACE. A genetically engineered being WILL be constantly in your face, that's enough to cause bad things to happen.<br>
-------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
The things I mentioned are more than concepts, they are actions.  People who believe that cows are sentient see everyone that is eating beef as &quot;constantly in their face.&quot;  People who are poor could see people who are rich as &quot;constantly in their face.&quot;  People who are pro-life see those who have abortions as &quot;constantly in their face.&quot;<br>
<br>
There are MANY, hard-lined divisions that exist in the world.  Very few of them ever lead to war.  And the ones that did usually resulted from a lack of understanding, not from a real conflict. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uevantineessidel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evantine Essidel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://evantine.homestead.com/files/Eventine.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 1:14:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cloning</span><hr size=1> Once upon a time, it was wrong and against the law to own a telescope. People were killed because they watched the sun and moon orbits and reported what they saw. Cloning raises a lot of moral questions for me, but I will never say it shouldnt be done. You can cry about how this is different from that and a million other situations of &quot;morality vs science&quot;, but its not.<br>
<br>
That's not to say it can't be used for evil intent. Look at how Hitler warped Darwin's theories into justifying racial cleansing. But that doesnt mean that it was wrong to research evolution. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udryfft.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dryfft</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 1:15:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT:  Cloning</span><hr size=1> Whizbang,<br>
<br>
I'm not sure what you're arguing for anymore.  Could you just give a quick and dirty? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unyargle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyargle</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 1:16:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT:  Cloning</span><hr size=1> &quot;The things I mentioned are more than concepts, they are actions. People who believe that cows are sentient see everyone that is eating beef as &quot;constantly in their face.&quot; People who are poor could see people who are rich as &quot;constantly in their face.&quot; People who are pro-life see those who have abortions as &quot;constantly in their face.&quot;&quot;<br>
