But destroying defection will let the real human shine through, instead of the disease. That's why I support this form of genetic engineering.<br>
<br>
HOWEVER, a world where babies are designed according to their parents' wims, a world where babies of the rich are actually BETTER than the babies of the poor, not just better educated and better nourished, is not a nice, happy world. Advances in technology are slowly but surely diminishing the amount of the world's population that lives in poverty. Would you throw a huge wrench into this, creating a whole new caste division, not between rich and poor but between human and superhuman?<br>
<br>
I wouldn't. <p><center>
<img src="http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin2.jpg">
</center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uszrazzt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Szrazzt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 1:20:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT:  Cloning</span><hr size=1> It really seems that those who are against this are more afraid of loosing out to this superhuman race. That race is our (read yours and mine) children and just because they don't have all of my genes doesn't mean that they are superhuman. <br>
<br>
Superhuman by definition means that someone is better than a human. Seeing as what most people have been talking about is people with no genetic defects (or custom colored eyes or hair or what ever other superficial characteristic you wish to modify) I don't see how this is superhuman. My eyes are Hazel but say I wanted a child with blue eyes. Just because I did not provide the DNA for blue eyes doesn't mean that its not possible for a human to have them. It is possible for people to be born without a genetic defect therefor eliminating defects prior to their manifestation is also within the realm of Human and not Superhuman.<br>
<br>
Genetic engineering can basically thought of as maximizing your child's potential and I don't know a parent who does not think this is a good thing. Some would say this is too far, I'll leave that to the individual to decide though and not the government or the UN.<br>
<br>
The human race has been creating Caste systems, Strict social structures and class systems which do suck for the people in the lower levels. Engineering &quot;better&quot; people only changes why you are in the lower levels not the fact that you are there. It won't even change the position you are born in. If your parents are rich you'll have these advantages. If your parents are poor you won't. No change in status quo.<br>
<br>
This won't change the fact that rich kids get nice little pieces of paper from Ivy league schools which grant them high paying jobs and opens doors for them. What it might do is make the kid intelligent enough that they keep the job due to their qualifications and not their cash.<br>
<br>
